00:00:51.450 --> 00:00:56.450
I am so thankful to Jehovah for this arrangement.

00:00:56.450 --> 00:01:00.450
Perhaps you can relate to her expressions.

00:01:00.450 --> 00:01:09.450
Thank you for the generous donations you have made online at donate.jw.org and by other means,

00:01:09.450 --> 00:01:13.450
which help make these streaming services possible.

00:01:13.450 --> 00:01:24.659
During these critical last days, many families lack the affection the Jehovah designed us to give and receive.

00:01:24.659 --> 00:01:32.659
However, God's word contains principles that, when followed, lead to peace.

00:01:32.659 --> 00:01:40.659
Resture you will enjoy the fine talks and dramatizations in this next symposium.

00:01:40.659 --> 00:01:46.659
Brother Joel Dellinger, a helper to the service committee, will deliver the first talk,

00:01:46.659 --> 00:02:00.140
follow the roadmap to family peace, show love and respect.

00:02:00.140 --> 00:02:03.140
Family peace is precious.

00:02:03.140 --> 00:02:13.139
It's even as the Bible proverb says, better is a piece of dry bread where there is peace than a house full of feasting along with quarreling.

00:02:13.139 --> 00:02:17.139
But what exactly is family peace?

00:02:17.139 --> 00:02:22.139
Someone might say, as long as we're not arguing, our families at peace.

00:02:22.139 --> 00:02:25.139
But is that real peace?

00:02:25.139 --> 00:02:30.139
We might think of two countries that we're fighting but have now agreed to a ceasefire.

00:02:30.139 --> 00:02:35.139
Does the ceasefire mean that they've become real friends who love one another?

00:02:35.139 --> 00:02:37.139
No.

00:02:37.139 --> 00:02:40.139
We know that genuine peace takes more work.

00:02:40.139 --> 00:02:43.139
That's true in the family as well.

00:02:43.139 --> 00:02:51.139
Our Heavenly Father knows that the most satisfying family peace involves more than an absence of arguing.

00:02:51.139 --> 00:02:56.139
It involves a family's well-being and unity.

00:02:56.139 --> 00:03:01.139
Is such peace in a family today really possible?

00:03:01.139 --> 00:03:06.139
Although none of us have a perfect family, the answer is yes.

00:03:06.139 --> 00:03:16.139
While it requires work, perhaps breaking bad habits that disrupt peace and adopting new ones that promote it, those efforts are worth it.

00:03:16.139 --> 00:03:29.139
In this symposium, we'll see how Bible principles can guide families to peace, just as a roadmap guides travelers to a beautiful destination.

00:03:29.139 --> 00:03:43.139
In each of the talks, we invite you husbands, fathers, wives, mothers, children, teenagers to be the traveler who studies the map and then goes in the right direction.

00:03:43.139 --> 00:03:49.139
The focus of our first talk is showing love and respect.

00:03:49.139 --> 00:03:55.139
Why would you say these two qualities are so important to family peace?

00:03:55.139 --> 00:03:57.139
Well, it's simple.

00:03:57.139 --> 00:04:03.139
Because family members who love and respect one another feel secure and appreciated.

00:04:03.139 --> 00:04:10.139
As a result, our relationships are warm, close, and peaceful.

00:04:10.139 --> 00:04:14.139
