00:11:05.860 --> 00:11:07.860
We should make amends quickly.

00:11:07.860 --> 00:11:10.860
A mother named Marina said this.

00:11:10.860 --> 00:11:13.860
We tried to set a good example for our children

00:11:13.860 --> 00:11:16.860
and forgiving others and not getting offended.

00:11:16.860 --> 00:11:19.860
When I am wrong, I apologize to my children.

00:11:19.860 --> 00:11:25.860
I want them to learn to do the same in their dealings with others.

00:11:25.860 --> 00:11:28.860
That's a good habit, wouldn't you agree?

00:11:28.860 --> 00:11:31.860
Well, let's consider one more, a fourth habit.

00:11:31.860 --> 00:11:35.860
Help your family members feel respected.

00:11:35.860 --> 00:11:40.860
An article in the Awake magazine once made this insightful comment.

00:11:40.860 --> 00:11:44.860
Respect is in the eye of the beholder.

00:11:44.860 --> 00:11:46.860
What does that mean?

00:11:46.860 --> 00:11:49.860
Even if we think we're showing respect in the family,

00:11:49.860 --> 00:11:52.860
a good question to ask ourselves is,

00:11:52.860 --> 00:11:56.860
do my family members feel that I respect them?

00:11:56.860 --> 00:11:59.860
Is there more I can do to help my mate, my children,

00:11:59.860 --> 00:12:04.860
or my parents feel loved and respected?

00:12:04.860 --> 00:12:09.860
Brothers and sisters, when we fulfill our God-given role in the family

00:12:09.860 --> 00:12:12.860
by developing good habits such as these,

00:12:12.860 --> 00:12:17.860
we show respect both for Jehovah and all of our family members.

